docs.abstract: It is less clear that tech executives’ strategy of evasive answers will continue to work now that lawmakers have begun doing their homework.
docs.snippet: It is less clear that tech executives’ strategy of evasive answers will continue to work now that lawmakers have begun doing their homework.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Mark Zuckerberg appeared in front of Congress two years ago, the Facebook chief executive’s memorable retort to a clueless questioner was “Senator, we run ads.” After Wednesday’s marathon appearance by Mr. Zuckerberg and three other tech titans at a House hearing on competition in the tech industry, a more fitting quote might be “Congresswoman, I’m not sure what you would mean by ‘threaten.’”

docs.abstract: Life will return to ‘normal,’ but not entirely. Here are some suggestions for investing in a changed world.
docs.snippet: Life will return to ‘normal,’ but not entirely. Here are some suggestions for investing in a changed world.
docs.lead_paragraph: When facing a crisis as dire as the coronavirus pandemic, it’s natural to think that everything will change utterly and forever by the time it’s over. But people are resilient creatures of habit, so many aspects of life will return to what used to pass for “normal.”
